{
  format: 1
  name: conflicting-key-and-set-markers-unspecified
  suite: static
  tags: [grammar, shape-markers, adversarial]
  // Attack: put two contradictory shape markers on one object to see which one
  // wins (or whether the object is smuggled past validation). Annex C.2 lists
  // '$key' (keyed collection) and '$set' (unique set) as distinct shape markers
  // and says "A plain object WITHOUT a shape marker is a static struct" — it
  // describes zero-marker and single-marker cases but never states what a
  // MULTIPLY-marked object means or that it is invalid. §5.4 defines $key and
  // §5.5 defines $set independently; neither forbids their co-occurrence.
  note: "Annex C.2 enumerates shape markers and defines the zero-marker case (static struct) but does not state whether an object bearing two mutually exclusive markers ($key and $set) is invalid or how it is interpreted. §5.4 and §5.5 define each marker in isolation. The outcome is not deducible from SPEC.md."
  spec: ["#annex-c", "§C.2", "#state-model", "§5.4", "§5.5"]

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.twomarkers@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      things: {
        $key: "id"
        $set: "text"
        id: "text"
      }
    }
  }

  expect: {
    outcome: unspecified
  }
}
